// PART 3: Matthew MacDougall

https://youtu.be/Kbk9BiPhm7o?si=Bathz9orrYzJo_Mj&t=13149
from 3:39:09 to 5:06:11

- Matthew MacDougall, the head neurosurgeon at Neuralink
- goes over his background from neuroscience to neurosurgery
  - started studying neuroscience then went to medical school
  - talk about the great surgeons he met
- neurosurgeons work really hard, long hours, relentlessly decades after decades
to reach excellence
- to build a great team you need people able to passionately defend their ideas,
but still able to give up on some, to make the team win

